<topic id="author-docbook5-extensions" >
  <title>DocBook 5 Author Actions</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords><indexterm>DocBook V5 Document Type<indexterm>Author extensions</indexterm></indexterm></keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>A variety of actions are available in the DocBook 4 framework that can be added to the
        <uicontrol>DocBook5</uicontrol> menu, the <uicontrol>Author custom actions</uicontrol>
      toolbar, the contextual menu, and the <uicontrol>Content Completion Assistant</uicontrol>. The
      following default actions are included in the toolbar and the <uicontrol>DocBook5</uicontrol>
      menu and are readily available when editing in <uicontrol>Author</uicontrol> mode (most of
      them are also available, by default, in the contextual menu):<dl>
        <dlentry conref="author-docbook4-extensions.dita#author-docbook4-extensions/bold-dlentry">
          <dt/>
          <dd/>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry conref="author-docbook4-extensions.dita#author-docbook4-extensions/italic-dlentry">
          <dt/>
          <dd/>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry
          conref="author-docbook4-extensions.dita#author-docbook4-extensions/underline-dlentry">
          <dt/>
          <dd/>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><uicontrol><image href="../img/LinkDrop.png" id="image_uq1_hkx_sr"/>Link</uicontrol>
            Actions Drop-Down Menu</dt>
          <dd>
            <p>The following link actions are available from this menu:<dl>
                <dlentry>
                  <dt><uicontrol>Cross reference (link)</uicontrol></dt>
                  <dd>Inserts a hypertext link.</dd>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry>
                  <dt><uicontrol>Cross reference (xref)</uicontrol></dt>
                  <dd>Inserts a cross reference to another part of the document.</dd>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry>
                  <dt><uicontrol>Web Link (link)</uicontrol></dt>
                  <dd>Inserts a link that addresses its target with a URL (Universal Resource
                    Locator).</dd>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry>
                  <dt><?oxy_comment_start author="steven_higgs" timestamp="20150529T172140+0300" comment="Ask if there are any differences for DocBook5, as per the universal olinking in DocBook 5 section at the bottom of http://www.sagehill.net/docbookxsl/Olinking.html"?><uicontrol>Insert
                      Olink</uicontrol><?oxy_comment_end?></dt>
                  <dd>Opens the <uicontrol>Insert Olink</uicontrol> dialog box that allows you to
                    insert a link that addresses its target indirectly, using the
                      <codeph>targetdoc</codeph> and <codeph>targetptr</codeph> values that are
                    present in a <xref href="author-docbook-targetset-doc-type.dita"
                        ><uicontrol>Targetset</uicontrol></xref> file.<fig product="author editor"
                      id="fig_hsm_xwg_wq">
                      <title>Insert OLink Dialog Box</title>
                      <image href="../img/sa_insert_olink.png" placement="inline"
                        id="image_ytm_xwg_wq"/>
                    </fig><fig product="authorEclipse editorEclipse" id="fig_h5m_xwg_wq">
                      <title>Insert OLink Dialog Box</title>
                      <image href="../img/ec_insert_olink.png" placement="inline"
                        id="image_zvm_xwg_wq"/>
                    </fig><p>After you choose the <uicontrol>Targetset URL</uicontrol>, the
                      structure of the target documents is presented. For each target document
                        (<codeph>targetdoc</codeph>), its content is displayed allowing you to
                      easily identify the <codeph>targetptr</codeph> for the <codeph>olink</codeph>
                      element that will be inserted. You can also use the search fields to quickly
                      identify a target. If you already know the values for
                        <uicontrol>targetdoc</uicontrol> and <uicontrol>targetptr</uicontrol>, you
                      can insert them directly in the corresponding fields. You can also edit an
                        <codeph>olink</codeph> using the <uicontrol>Edit OLink</uicontrol> action
                      that is available on the contextual menu. The last used
                        <uicontrol>Targetset</uicontrol> URL will be used to identify the edited
                      target.</p></dd>
                  <dd>To insert XREF text into the <codeph>olink</codeph>, enter the text in the
                      <uicontrol>xreftext</uicontrol> field and make sure the <uicontrol>Insert
                      xreftext in the OLink</uicontrol> option is enabled.</dd>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry>
                  <dt><uicontrol>Insert URI</uicontrol></dt>
                  <dd>Inserts an URI element. The URI identifies a Uniform Resource Identifier (URI)
                    in content.</dd>
                </dlentry>
              </dl></p>
          </dd>
